# Gateway - Trivy image-scan accepted-risks list.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Each CVE below was CRITICAL+fixable when Trivy flagged it, but the fix
# lives in an UPSTREAM image we don't build. We accept the risk until the
# upstream maintainer publishes a rebuild, or we bump the tag.
#
# REVIEW CADENCE: first Monday of every quarter. When reviewing:
#   1. Re-run `gh run rerun <latest> --failed` to refresh the list.
#   2. For each CVE still listed, check whether upstream has published a
#      new image tag or an advisory marking it non-exploitable in this
#      deployment (e.g. SSH code paths in Loki we never reach).
#   3. Delete anything that's been fixed; CI will tell you if a new one
#      appears that isn't listed.
# LAST REVIEWED: 2026-04-19 (initial list from CI run 24614331823)
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Go stdlib / toolchain (present in every Go-based image) ---
# Loki, Promtail, Prometheus, Alertmanager, Grafana, Redpanda, etc. ship
# statically-linked Go binaries whose stdlib version is fixed at image
# build time. Each of these is resolved by a rebuild with Go >=1.22.4 / 1.24.13.
CVE-2024-24790        # net/netip: IPv4-in-IPv6 Is* misbehavior
CVE-2025-68121        # crypto/tls: cert validation during session resumption
CVE-2026-27497        # stdlib
CVE-2026-27498        # stdlib
CVE-2026-28292        # stdlib
CVE-2026-33660        # stdlib
CVE-2026-33696        # stdlib
CVE-2026-33863        # stdlib
CVE-2026-33864        # stdlib

# --- golang.org/x/crypto ---
# SSH server-side bug in PublicKeyCallback. Gateway containers do not
# expose SSH server paths using this library, but the binary still embeds it.
CVE-2024-45337

# --- google.golang.org/grpc ---
# HTTP/2 path-validation authz bypass in grpc-go authz middleware. We don't
# use grpc-go authz middleware directly; upstream services that embed it
# (e.g. Loki, Promtail) will fix on rebuild.
CVE-2026-33186

# --- github.com/docker/docker (moby) ---
# Auth regression; only reachable through Docker API. The Go binary inside
# Promtail embeds this transitively. Promtail does not expose a docker
# socket server - it only reads /var/run/docker.sock as a client.
CVE-2024-41110

# --- Debian base images (postgres-exporter path, promtail) ---
# Krb5 + libsasl2 + OpenSSL chain. We don't use GSSAPI / Kerberos auth to
# Postgres or Redis in this stack. OpenSSL issues are primarily TLS server
# paths; our TLS terminates at Kong, which uses its own OpenSSL build.
CVE-2024-37371        # krb5 GSS message token
CVE-2023-24538        # older Go text/template (promtail)
CVE-2023-24540        # older Go text/template (promtail)
CVE-2023-36665        # (promtail)

# --- Node.js / npm (n8n image) ---
# n8nio/n8n:1.28.0 ships a pinned Node runtime. Listed CVEs land via Node
# stdlib or bundled npm packages. Risk-mitigated because n8n is
# loopback-only behind Kong auth and does not parse untrusted user code
# outside the workflow editor (which is admin-authenticated).
CVE-2024-21508
CVE-2024-21511
CVE-2024-8986
CVE-2025-7783
CVE-2025-9288
CVE-2025-15467
CVE-2025-29774
CVE-2025-29775
CVE-2025-47949
CVE-2025-62718
CVE-2025-65964
CVE-2025-68613
CVE-2025-68668
CVE-2026-1470
CVE-2026-21877
CVE-2026-21893
CVE-2026-25049
CVE-2026-25052
CVE-2026-25053
CVE-2026-25056
CVE-2026-25115
CVE-2026-25896
CVE-2026-27493
CVE-2026-27495
CVE-2026-27577
CVE-2026-33937
CVE-2026-40175
